</tr>
</tbody>
</table></div>
<p>The distinction matters. Old SEO tutorials still teach <code>link:</code> even though Google retired it in 2017. We mark every deprecated operator below so you do not waste queries.</p>
<p>Operators are case-insensitive except for <code>OR</code> and <code>AND</code>, which must be uppercase. They are also space-sensitive. The syntax <code>site:example.com</code> works. The syntax <code>site: example.com</code> does not.</p>
